## Grid Basics Review
Brief overview of fundamental grid concepts:
- `display: grid` - Creates a grid container
- Grid lines, tracks, and cells
- Grid columns and rows
- Explicit vs implicit grid

## Advanced Properties

### Grid Template Properties
- `grid-template-columns` - Define column sizes
- `grid-template-rows` - Define row sizes
- `grid-template-areas` - Create named grid areas
- `grid-template` - Shorthand property

### Item Placement
- `grid-column` - Span columns
- `grid-row` - Span rows
- `grid-placement` - Shorthand property
- `grid-auto-flow` - Control auto-placement

### Alignment Properties
- `justify-items` - Horizontal alignment
- `align-items` - Vertical alignment
- `justify-content` - Distribute columns
- `align-content` - Distribute rows

### Gap Properties
- `grid-gap` / `gap` - Space between items
- `column-gap` - Space between columns
- `row-gap` - Space between rows

## Layout Patterns
Common CSS Grid patterns and use cases:
- Holy Grail Layout
- Card Grid Layouts
- Responsive Image Galleries
- Dashboard Layouts

## Responsive Design
- Using `auto-fit` and `auto-fill`
- `minmax()` function for flexible grids
- Media queries with grid
- Mobile-first approach

## Best Practices
- Use meaningful grid names
- Keep grid declarations readable
- Test across browsers
- Combine Grid with Flexbox appropriately
- Plan your layout before coding

